
[1]proposal

   PROPO'SAL, n. s as z. [from propose.]

   1. That which is offered or propounded for consideration or acceptance;
   a scheme or design, terms or conditions proposed; as, to make proposals
   for a treaty of peace; to offer proposals for erecting a building; to
   make proposals of marriage; proposals for subscription to a loan or to
   a literary work.

   2. Offer to the mind; as the proposal of an agreeable object.
